HEADWORD: Vacatur
<hw>Va*ca"tur</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., it is made
void, fr. L. <ets>vacare</ets> to be empty. See <er>Vacant</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>An order of court by which a proceeding is set
aside or annulled.</def>⟦br⟧
